<subSubSection id="8E963870534355A8735A00756A33C494" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph id="6912DF4B5E545F23CAC23BF95C8A41B9" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4463E731ECD27BE3BA7D160AFC70ECBC" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">
It is still doubted whether 
<taxonomicName id="3E96D6B9D60839850179706361B02901" authorityName="Raf., New Fl. [Rafinesque] 4: 16" authorityYear="1836" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis id="FFAD9AA423B01035E85A93347B46F875" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Sesuvium verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="291102A2119CC00BB06FD235DCCC7CB2" author="Rafinesque, CS" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="35" pageNumber="80" refId="B64" refString="Rafinesque, CS, 1836. New flora and botany of North America, Part 4. [Printed for the author and publisher], Philadelphia." title="New flora and botany of North America, Part 4. [Printed for the author and publisher], Philadelphia." year="1836">Rafinesque 1836</bibRefCitation>
) is the oldest name for this taxon. Three older names- 
<taxonomicName id="9062D0D9A78D5F837313728296FB2FC6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium revolutifolium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutifolium">
<emphasis id="D9455E0463BFD1A675A3565CB39D49C6" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Sesuvium revolutifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ortega from Cuba (
<bibRefCitation id="D85A29FE3399ECCB7AF305355512DAFF" author="Ortega, CG" journalOrPublisher="2, 2 (10). Borntraeger, Berlin" pageId="35" pageNumber="80" refId="B61" refString="Ortega, CG, 1797. Novarum, aut rariorum plantarum horti regii botanici Matritensis descriptionum decades, cum nonnullarum iconibus. Typ. Ibarrriana, Madrid." title="Novarum, aut rariorum plantarum horti regii botanici Matritensis descriptionum decades, cum nonnullarum iconibus. Typ. Ibarrriana, Madrid." year="1797">Ortega 1797</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="F555929EFFC8D983AFC0F718F7EC211F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis id="BDCD4D72EBD944EF654A46FCAF538D6A" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">S. revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pers. and 
<taxonomicName id="64677877B87F0D5B724F5CF7AE4DB858" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">
<emphasis id="C378F3AD665C9B035EEF2CB379F027CF" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">S. sessile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pers. (
<bibRefCitation id="C04C8C01680FAF84C468C33F6D72AD3C" author="Persoon, CH" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="35" pageNumber="80" refId="B63" refString="Persoon, CH, 1806. Synopsis Plantarum: seu Enchiridium botanicum, complectens enumerationem systematicam specierum hucusque cognitarum, Vol. 2, part 1. Cramer, Paris." title="Synopsis Plantarum: seu Enchiridium botanicum, complectens enumerationem systematicam specierum hucusque cognitarum, Vol. 2, part 1. Cramer, Paris." year="1806">Persoon 1806</bibRefCitation>
), both of unknown origin-may be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="2F04D5E6AD07F3CAAF05B5CB7F566547" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis id="9A4F4A7243E201A52FE8A1EEABB3876E" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">S. verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the 
<pageBreakToken id="DCD211F649254B4FBD107859410AE6D4" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" start="start">description</pageBreakToken>
of both 
<taxonomicName id="F08BB2C5E5AA2E23AE254DC143793281" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis id="302150F7F1F347B0FD2F4C81C7860D4A" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C9213B666E1DC3B1402CD18EC8C358BA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">
<emphasis id="BFCAB21AF67CDE23C475B39963B5330E" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. sessile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very short and poor and no original material could be traced. The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="E47F25315EDED277A1072A66FCC5B180" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutifolium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutifolium">
<emphasis id="75BCAA361237D9E96E0B254FF2EF9C55" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. revolutifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
completely matches the habit of 
<taxonomicName id="EE8A2D00CE85580FA57E010949B8F586" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis id="2B0979CA428BE17C3D95644F778AE1B7" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is not sure whether the plants from North America are identical to those from Cuba. 
<taxonomicName id="BE654D6E6A0DAFBF0E98A295DBCA615C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium revolutifolium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutifolium">
<emphasis id="CC4C5C41553B0464D473519C67C40FA1" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">Sesuvium revolutifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9DE0966336905E15962786B07D0960A2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">
<emphasis id="2CD860327BE2558FC61BBF80B7694C4C" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. sessile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="31EC91985C0DB17FAC6032AD0A415E47" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis id="5AEF2CB1C874BAAEBD6601725A7002B8" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been synonymised with 
<taxonomicName id="840CB4297929B7E3666BF9BB00DA39C2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. portulacastrum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="portulacastrum">
<emphasis id="F4EC339612C5708EB2E3B8FFC0A012A6" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. portulacastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="FF7FD0C6C707C471B4275FB7CA348592" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" author="Bohley, K" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" pagination="124 - 147" refId="B9" refString="Bohley, K, Winter, PJD, Kadereit, G, 2017. A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae). Systematic Botany 42 (1): 124 - 147, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" title="A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" volume="42" year="2017">Bohley et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, but the nomenclature of all three species needs further study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACC65D19FFF0093C1DF31A0DA5C4E149" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="2410022CF077FB292206ED75CAE485E0" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FB61E5EA0D27E3E128A4DDBC094AC29" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">
The most indicative characters of this species are: 1) perennial life history, 2) presence of abundant papillae on stems and leaves, 3) 
<taxonomicName id="BCD5D6801D4F8267BC230E17B57948AB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">Sesuvium sessile</taxonomicName>
turbinate flower buds and capsules and 4) clearly expressed detachments of the aril from the seed coat. Usually, the stems are rooting; however 
<bibRefCitation id="BDD9F2A933690E1BEE87AC316FDBB746" author="Ferren, WR" journalOrPublisher="4. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford" pageId="33" pageNumber="78" pagination="80 - 81" refId="B20" refString="Ferren, WR, 2003. Sesuvium. In: Flora of North America, North of Mexico, Vol. 4. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford: 80 - 81" title="Sesuvium." volumeTitle="Flora of North America, North of Mexico, Vol." year="2003">Ferren (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="04D306A53A1498AC1C75FF6E85706BD2" author="Baldwin, BG" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" refId="B6" refString="Baldwin, BG, Goldman, DH, Keil, DJ, Patterson, R, Rosatti, TJ, Wilken, DH, 2012. The Jepson Manual: Vascular plants of California. University of California Press, Berkeley, Lon Angeles, London." title="The Jepson Manual: Vascular plants of California. University of California Press, Berkeley, Lon Angeles, London." year="2012">Baldwin et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="1094025C0B0E02EEC163EF30BD8709EC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis id="94E921EB9F4931BED72930590C12377F" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a non-rooting plant (probably applicable to younger plants, as observed in the specimen from Cape Verde listed below). For detailed morphological description, see 
<bibRefCitation id="9C77363B7DCDB0AC2CE75647F8CD7E6C" author="Fadaie, F" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Botany" pageId="33" pageNumber="78" pagination="87 - 88" refId="B19" refString="Fadaie, F, Attar, F, Ghahreman, A, 2006. A new record of Aizoaceae (Sesuvium verrucosum Raf.) for the flora of Iran. Iranian Journal of Botany 12 (1): 87 - 88" title="A new record of Aizoaceae (Sesuvium verrucosum Raf.) for the flora of Iran." volume="12" year="2006">Fadaie et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="046E4BC80425946BDAE7DE8A6EFEFFAC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" author="Bohley, K" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" pagination="124 - 147" refId="B9" refString="Bohley, K, Winter, PJD, Kadereit, G, 2017. A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae). Systematic Botany 42 (1): 124 - 147, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" title="A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" volume="42" year="2017">Bohley et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="323B668C355BF8FC3CCC2C0FA5F541F4" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" type="examined specimens">
<paragraph id="18FCEE9C18F078FB4CD388F36DDCDC0A" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">Examined specimens.</paragraph>
